meta {
  name: GET parking position (v3, formatted address)
  type: http
  seq: 23
}

get {
  url: {{base_url}}/api/v3/maps/positions/vehicles/{{vin}}/parking
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  Last known parking position. Response shape:
    {"parkingPosition": {
       "gpsCoordinates": {"latitude": <float>, "longitude": <float>},
       "formattedAddress": "Bünzweg 16, 5504 Othmarsingen, Schweiz",
       "carCapturedTimestamp": "..."
     }}

  v3 (vs v2) gained the ``formattedAddress`` field — a backend-side
  reverse-geocode so we don't need to ship a Nominatim caller.

  Drives device_tracker.<vin> (lat/lon) and
  sensor.<vin>_parking_address.

  Implementation: gathered in SkodaClient.get_status() at
  custom_components/vag_connect/cariad/api/skoda.py:154; parsed at
  the parking branch around line 313.
}
